																		hot take: beer is just bread-flavored lacroix
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203534" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1536285133 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Sep 2018 01:52</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3960274">
									

<p>After ch00bakka posted <a href="/about-deer">About Deer</a>, I kept telling them they needed to write one about the various silly social media posts that would inevitably spring from such a school. Today I sent them a few Facebook posts I thought would give them inspiration, including &quot;hot take: beer is just bread-flavored lacroix&quot;.</p>
<p>Then we started shitposting about lacroix, and the rest is history.</p>
<p>Huge thanks to ch00bakka for doing all the heavy lifting like importing the tweet formatting (courtesy of <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>) and doing the handles, images, and timestamps. I would never have the patience for that stuff and thus could never have written this without them.</p>
<p>Also wow, I just realized that this is my 50th article for the site. Crazy how that happens.</p>

